content:
Einstein Bots are built for conversation. To make setup a breeze, some of the most common dialogs are included with each new bot. These dialogs allow you to quickly transfer conversations to an agent, or gracefully end a chat. You can customize each message to your companyâ€™s voice and tone.

System dialogs are essential functions that help a conversation move smoothly. The following system dialogs are automatically loaded with each new bot:

Confused Dialog: helps address requests that are out of scope for your bot.
End Chat dialog: ends a conversation, thanking the customer and prompting them to manually end it in standard bots or automatically closing it in enhanced bots.
Error Handler dialog: delivers a message if an error occurs inside the conversation.
Main Menu dialog: sent to customers after the Welcome Dialog, allowing them to go back to the main menu.
No Agent dialog: sends a message to customers if no agents are available, supporting Chat and Messaging channels only.
Transfer to Agent dialog: automatically transfers conversations from bots to agents in standard bots or uses the default outbound Omni-Channel flow in enhanced bots.
Welcome dialog: the first dialog sent to customers interacting with a bot.

System dialogs can vary based on how you create your bot. Existing bots can assign dialogs to these functions by setting a dialog. System dialogs are essential for guiding the bot through conversation flow, and you can assign custom dialogs as system dialogs to customize the experience.
title: Understanding Einstein Bots System Dialogs
